  • Interface Summary
    Interface
    Description
    Contained<T extends Container>
    An interface for objects which are contained in any kind of Container
    Container
    An ancestor class for any kind of SystemComponent / SystemRelation container.
    Containing<T extends Container>
    An interface for objects that represent a container
    Described<T>
    Interface for container which have a hierarchical view counterpart (ie are represented by a SystemComponent).
    DynamicContainer<T>
    An interface for containers which must delay addition and deletion of items up to a given step
    NestedContainer<T>
    An interface for methods to add to a container to make it hierarchical (ie containing subcontainers)
    NestedDynamicContainer<T>
    A complement to dynamicContainer for nested containers
    ResettableContainer<T>
    An interface for containers that can be reset to an initial state.
    SimpleContainer<T>
    A container for 3Worlds runtime items
